## 4. EVM local payment lacks live Alchemy regression coverage

Status: **blocked** (no Alchemy API key in dev environment)

The built-in `evm-local` payment path is covered by Rust unit tests for amount calculation and compile-time checks, but real-chain acceptance (BSC USDT payment, amount mismatch rejection, same-amount multi-address concurrency) requires a live Alchemy API key and manual test funds. Mark blocked until credentials are available.

Acceptance checklist (manual, when key is provided):

- [ ] BSC USDT small payment confirms order
- [ ] Underpaid transfer is rejected
- [ ] Same-amount concurrent payments to different addresses resolve correctly
- [ ] Overpay tolerance (if enabled) behaves as configured
- [ ] Manual `tx_hash` confirmation path works

References:

- `src/services/evm_local_service.rs`
- `schema/0012_evm_local_payments.sql`
- `docs/README.md`: EVM 本地收款

